00:00:00.370 --> 00:00:11.099
Why does Breathing Helium Changes the Sound
of Your Voice?

00:00:11.099 --> 00:00:15.099
The air in your lungs gets pushed up by the
relaxation of your diaphragm.

00:00:15.099 --> 00:00:20.410
It then goes through your trachea and out
a small orifice that has two folds of skin

00:00:20.410 --> 00:00:24.020
(vocal cords) on either side of it, in the
shape of a V.

00:00:24.020 --> 00:00:26.480
This is called your larynx or voice box.

00:00:26.480 --> 00:00:31.350
As the muscles that attach to your voice box
tense and relax, they create a vibration of

00:00:31.350 --> 00:00:32.369
the cords.

00:00:32.369 --> 00:00:35.489
As these cords vibrate, they release pulses
of air.

00:00:35.489 --> 00:00:39.010
The tension in these muscles creates the differences
in frequency.

00:00:39.010 --> 00:00:43.969
The higher the tension, the higher the frequency
and therefore the higher the pitch.

00:00:43.969 --> 00:00:48.519
This frequency is measured in hertz (how many
times a second this repeats).

00:00:48.519 --> 00:00:52.969
For example, nearly all human speech sounds
usually range from approx.

00:00:52.969 --> 00:00:55.519
200 hertz-8,000 hertz.

00:00:55.519 --> 00:00:58.579
Meaning the sound waves vibrate at approx.

00:00:58.579 --> 00:01:00.750
200-8,000 times per sec.

00:01:00.750 --> 00:01:05.370
Once out of the voice box, the air travels
into the area of your mouth that can be informally

00:01:05.370 --> 00:01:07.430
known as your vocal tract.

00:01:07.430 --> 00:01:12.630
As you manipulate your tongue, jaw and lips,
you can change the resonant frequencies created

00:01:12.630 --> 00:01:17.850
by your vocal cords, allowing you to make
the many different sounds of speech.

00:01:17.850 --> 00:01:23.240
Together, the sound we hear created by air
flowing at different frequencies and resonances,

00:01:23.240 --> 00:01:24.420
creates our voice.

00:01:24.420 --> 00:01:28.480
One other factor affecting pitch is the thickness
of ones vocal cords.

00:01:28.480 --> 00:01:31.230
The thicker the folds of skin are, the deeper
the voice.

00:01:31.230 --> 00:01:35.490
This is due to the amount of mass your chords
have that the air has to manipulate.

00:01:35.490 --> 00:01:38.880
As you would expect then, men tend to have
much thicker folds of skin then women, ah

00:01:38.880 --> 00:01:39.880
the soulful folds of Barry White!!

